"use strict";(globalThis.webpackChunkinformationtoolbench=globalThis.webpackChunkinformationtoolbench||[]).push([[9206],{589(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"webapp-0.0.8","metadata":{"permalink":"/docs/changelog-webapp/webapp-0.0.8","source":"@site/changelog/webapp/2026-04-10-webapp-0.0.8/index.md","title":"0.0.8 (WebApp)","description":"We\'re excited to announce version 0.0.8 of the ITB WebApp, featuring 7 new advanced features and significant performance optimizations. This focused release brings sophisticated interaction patterns, customizable user preferences, and dramatically improved canvas performance for large-scale models.","date":"2026-04-10T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"ITB APP","permalink":"/docs/changelog-webapp/tags/app","description":"All changes related to the ITB Application"},{"inline":false,"label":"UI","permalink":"/docs/changelog-webapp/tags/ui","description":"User interface changes"},{"inline":false,"label":"Model","permalink":"/docs/changelog-webapp/tags/model","description":"Data model changes"},{"inline":true,"label":"performance","permalink":"/docs/changelog-webapp/tags/performance"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"slug":"webapp-0.0.8","title":"0.0.8 (WebApp)","authors":[],"tags":["app","ui","model","performance"]},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"0.0.7 (WebApp)","permalink":"/docs/changelog-webapp/webapp-0.0.7"}},"content":"We\'re excited to announce version 0.0.8 of the ITB WebApp, featuring 7 new advanced features and significant performance optimizations. This focused release brings sophisticated interaction patterns, customizable user preferences, and dramatically improved canvas performance for large-scale models.\\n\\n> **Part of ITB 0.0.8 release** - See [master release](/changelog/itb-0.0.8)\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## \u2728 New Features\\n\\n### \ud83c\udfaf Advanced Interaction Workflows\\n\\n#### 1. Drag Entity from Sidebar to Canvas\\n\\nAdd entities to viewpoints intuitively by dragging them directly from the left sidebar tree onto the modeling canvas. The grab cursor indicates draggable entities when a viewpoint is active.\\n\\n**Key Benefits:**\\n- More intuitive than context menu workflows\\n- Entities appear at the exact drop position\\n- Error handling prevents duplicate additions\\n- Existing context menu option remains available\\n\\n![Drag Entity to Canvas](./ui-010-new_drag-entity-to-canvas_001.png)\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### 2. Drag & Context Menu for Related Entities\\n\\nExplore and add related entities directly from the relations panel without manually searching in the sidebar tree. Right-click for context menu or drag to place on canvas.\\n\\n**Features:**\\n- Context menu for quick \\"Add to viewpoint\\" / \\"Remove from viewpoint\\"\\n- Drag and drop related entities onto canvas\\n- Works for all relation categories:\\n  - Outgoing entity relations\\n  - Incoming entity relations\\n  - Outgoing attribute relations\\n  - Incoming attribute relations\\n- Grab cursor indicates draggable rows when a viewpoint is active\\n\\n![Relation Drag and Context Menu](./ui-011-new_relation-drag-and-context-menu_001.png)\\n\\n![Relation Drag Example](./ui-011-new_relation-drag-and-context-menu_002.png)\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### 3. Comprehensive Canvas Context Menus\\n\\nRight-click anywhere on the canvas to access context-sensitive actions. Menus are available for:\\n\\n**Entity Node Headers:**\\n- Edit Entity\\n- Expand / Collapse Attributes\\n- Remove from Viewpoint\\n- Copy Source to Stage (ITB API)\\n- Delete Entity (with confirmation)\\n\\n![Entity Node Context Menu](./ui-012-new_canvas-context-menus_001.png)\\n\\n**Relation Edges:**\\n- Go to Source Entity\\n- Go to Target Entity\\n- Edit Relation\\n- Delete Relation (with confirmation)\\n- 20px invisible hit area makes thin edges easy to click\\n\\n![Relation Edge Context Menu](./ui-012-new_canvas-context-menus_002.png)\\n\\n**Canvas Background:**\\n- Deselect All\\n\\n![Canvas Background Context Menu](./ui-012-new_canvas-context-menus_003.png)\\n\\nAll delete actions show confirmation dialogs for safety.\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### 4. User Settings Dialog\\n\\nCentralized settings panel accessible via the gear icon in the header bar. All preferences are persisted to localStorage across sessions.\\n\\n**General Tab:**\\n- Language selection (English, German)\\n- Theme selection (Light, Dark, System)\\n\\n![User Settings - General Tab](./ui-014-new_user-settings-dialog_001.png)\\n\\n**Canvas Tab:**\\n- **Pan Mode** - Choose mouse button: Left Click (default), Right Click, or Middle Click\\n- **Background** - Dots, Lines, Cross, or None\\n- **Snap to Grid** - Toggle with adjustable grid size (10-50px)\\n- **Show Minimap** - Toggle minimap overlay\\n\\n![User Settings - Canvas Tab](./ui-014-new_user-settings-dialog_002.png)\\n\\n**Reset to Defaults** button available to restore original settings. All changes take effect immediately.\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### 5. Generate All Artifacts Button\\n\\nOne-click generation of all artifacts from the header bar. A modal dialog tracks progress through each step: preparing, saving, generating, with success/error feedback.\\n\\n**Workflow:**\\n1. Click the play icon button in header\\n2. Dialog automatically saves workspace data to backend\\n3. Backend generates all artifacts\\n4. Real-time progress indication\\n5. Auto-dismisses on completion or error\\n\\n![Generate All Artifacts Dialog](./ui-015-new_generate-all-button_001.png)\\n\\n*Only visible when backend supports generate-all endpoint.*\\n\\n---\\n\\n### \ud83c\udfaf Navigation & Discovery\\n\\n#### 6. Entity Tree Auto-Reveal on Canvas Selection\\n\\nSelecting an entity on the canvas automatically expands all parent folders in the left sidebar entity tree and scrolls the selected entity into view. Keeps sidebar and canvas perfectly in sync.\\n\\n**Behavior:**\\n- Auto-reveal disabled when search filter is active\\n- No redundant scrolling when selecting from tree directly\\n- Smooth scroll animation brings entity into view\\n\\n---\\n\\n### \u26a1 Performance Optimization\\n\\n#### 7. Comprehensive Canvas Rendering Performance Boost\\n\\nMassive performance improvements targeting large viewpoints. Initial render time for ~30 entities with ~40 edges dropped from ~25 seconds to under 10 seconds.\\n\\n**Key Optimizations:**\\n- **Viewport Culling** - Only visible nodes and edges are mounted in DOM\\n- **Shared Data Maps** - Entity types, attributes resolved once at canvas level instead of per-entity/edge\\n- **Structural Equality Guards** - Update arrays only when content changes\\n- **Debounced Viewpoint Switch** - Node and edge generation batched via requestAnimationFrame\\n- **Pre-resolved Edge Data** - All display data precomputed, eliminating per-edge store subscriptions\\n- **Lazy Edge Labels** - Labels hidden below 50% zoom\\n- **Cached Handle Positions** - Map lookups instead of linear searches\\n- **Inline SVG Icons** - Replaced component-based icons with inline SVG\\n- **Singleton Dialogs** - One shared AlertDialog and ContextMenu instance\\n- **Optimized CSS Transitions** - Scoped properties to avoid full layout recalculations\\n- **Automatic Minimap Optimization** - Auto-hides on viewpoints with 50+ entities\\n\\n**Results:**\\n- Faster viewpoint opening\\n- Smoother panning and zooming\\n- Faster viewpoint switching\\n- Significantly reduced jank\\n- Production-ready performance for real-world data models\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nITB WebApp 0.0.8 introduces powerful new interaction patterns and user customization options while delivering dramatic performance improvements. Advanced drag-and-drop workflows, contextual menus, and customizable settings enable sophisticated modeling workflows, while canvas rendering optimizations make large-scale data models responsive and usable.\\n\\nThank you to all contributors and users who provided feedback!"},{"id":"webapp-0.0.7","metadata":{"permalink":"/docs/changelog-webapp/webapp-0.0.7","source":"@site/changelog/webapp/2026-02-25-webapp-0.0.7/index.md","title":"0.0.7 (WebApp)","description":"We\'re excited to announce version 0.0.7 of the ITB WebApp (Information Technology Blueprint), bringing significant improvements to the user interface and data model capabilities. This release includes 10 new features and 1 important bug fix.","date":"2026-02-25T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"ITB APP","permalink":"/docs/changelog-webapp/tags/app","description":"All changes related to the ITB Application"},{"inline":false,"label":"UI","permalink":"/docs/changelog-webapp/tags/ui","description":"User interface changes"},{"inline":false,"label":"Model","permalink":"/docs/changelog-webapp/tags/model","description":"Data model changes"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"slug":"webapp-0.0.7","title":"0.0.7 (WebApp)","authors":[],"tags":["app","ui","model"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"0.0.8 (WebApp)","permalink":"/docs/changelog-webapp/webapp-0.0.8"}},"content":"We\'re excited to announce version 0.0.7 of the ITB WebApp (Information Technology Blueprint), bringing significant improvements to the user interface and data model capabilities. This release includes 10 new features and 1 important bug fix.\\n\\n> **Part of ITB 0.0.7 release** - See [master release](/changelog/itb-0.0.7) and [API Details](/changelog-api/api-0.0.7)\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## \u2728 New Features\\n\\n### UI Enhancements\\n\\nThis release brings substantial improvements to the user experience with 8 new UI features:\\n\\n#### 1. Model Filter for Entity Type\\n\\nFilter viewpoint displays by entity type to reduce visual complexity. A new funnel button in the model canvas toolbar allows you to toggle visibility of entity types, helping you focus on what matters most.\\n\\n**Key Benefits:**\\n- Improved readability of complex models\\n- Focus on relevant entity types\\n- Quick toggle on/off for each type\\n\\n![Model Filter for Entity Type](./ui-001-new_model-filter-entity-type_001.png)\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### 3. Add Entity to Center of Canvas\\n\\nEntities are now added to the center of the visible canvas area rather than at a fixed position, providing a more intuitive editing experience.\\n\\n![Add Entity to Center of Canvas](./ui-003-new_add-entity-to-center-of-canvas_001.png)\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### 4. Entity Usage Indicator Across Viewpoints\\n\\nNew visual indicator shows where entities are used across different viewpoints, making it easier to understand entity relationships and dependencies throughout your model.\\n\\n![Entity Usage Indicator](./ui-004-new_usage-of-enitity-in-viewpoints-indicator_001.png)\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### 5. Edge Highlighting for Selected Entity\\n\\nWhen selecting an entity, all connected edges are now highlighted, making it easier to trace relationships and understand connections at a glance.\\n\\n![Edge Highlighting for Selected Entity](./ui-005-new_edge-highlighting-for-selected-entity_001.png)\\n![Edge Highlighting Example 2](./ui-005-new_edge-highlighting-for-selected-entity_002.png)\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### 6. Attribute Drawer with Pagination\\n\\nThe drawer concept has been extended to attributes, now accessible via **CTRL+4**. All drawers (viewpoints, entities, relations, and attributes) are now paginated, significantly improving performance in large models.\\n\\n**Available Shortcuts:**\\n- **CTRL+1** - Viewpoints\\n- **CTRL+2** - Entities\\n- **CTRL+3** - Relations\\n- **CTRL+4** - Attributes (New!)\\n\\n![Attribute Drawer](./ui-006-new_attribute-drawer_001.png)\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### 7. Save Canvas as Image\\n\\nExport your viewpoint canvas as a high-quality image for documentation, presentations, or sharing with stakeholders.\\n\\n![Save Canvas as Image](./ui-007-new_save-canvas-as-image_001.png)\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### 8. Auto Arrange Canvas\\n\\nAutomatically arrange entities in your viewpoint for optimal layout. A layout algorithm now helps organize complex models with minimal manual effort.\\n\\n![Auto Arrange Canvas](./ui-008-new_auto-arrange-canvas_001.png)\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### 9. Resizable Left Sidebar\\n\\nThe left sidebar can now be resized to accommodate different screen sizes and user preferences, providing more flexibility in workspace organization.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Model Improvements\\n\\n#### 10. Mandatory Attribute Field\\n\\nAttributes can now be marked as mandatory using a new boolean field. This enhancement provides:\\n\\n- Clear documentation of required fields\\n- Better data quality and validation rules\\n- Support for generating database schemas with NOT NULL constraints\\n- Backward compatibility (defaults to `false`)\\n\\n**Display Features:**\\n- Visual indicator `*` (asterisk) in table columns to mark mandatory fields\\n- Compact icon-based display saves screen space compared to text labels\\n- Consistent indicator across main canvas, entity attributes table, and sidebar panels\\n\\n**Example:**\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\"id\\": \\"attr_123\\",\\n  \\"name\\": \\"customer_id\\",\\n  \\"type\\": \\"string\\",\\n  \\"mandatory\\": true,\\n  \\"description\\": \\"Unique customer identifier\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \ud83d\udc1e Bug Fixes\\n\\n### 2. Model Edge Routing on Collapse\\n\\nFixed an issue where edge routing was not properly updated when collapsing entity nodes in the canvas, ensuring proper visual representation of relationships.\\n\\n![Model Edge Routing on Collapse Fix](./ui-002-fix_model-edge-routing-on-collapse_001.png)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nVersion 0.0.7 represents a significant step forward in usability, performance, and data model capabilities. The UI improvements make working with large models more efficient, while the new mandatory field enhances data modeling best practices.\\n\\nThank you to all contributors and users who provided feedback!"}]}}')}}]);